ect, and listeners' religious experiences. Sounding Islam sheds new light on a key dimension of religion, the sonic incitement of sensations that are often difficult to translate into language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aAnthropology. 0aCommunication. Mass media. 0aIslamzMauritius. 0aIslamic poetry. 0aReligion (General). 0aSoundxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aVoice. 7aRELIGION / Islam / History.2bisacsh  aaffect.  aanthropology of media.  adevotional islam.  adimension of religion.  adivine manifestation.  aethnographic research.  ahistory of islam.  ainterplay of voice.  aislam.  aislamic rituals and practice.  amauritius.  amedia practices.  amedia.  amuslim.  aneo phenomenological.  areligion.  areligious experiences.  areligious traditions.  asonic dimensions.  asonic incitement of sensations.  asound studies.  atranslations.  avoice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520970762zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970762zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520970762.jpg  a978-3-11-066767-7 UC Press eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA